summary: Successfully merged feature branch (BinanceWebSocket with BTCPriceData) with main branch (technical indicators). Preserved both implementations to maintain full functionality.
strategyUsed: preserve-both-features: HEAD added BinanceWebSocket class using BTCPriceData model for real-time price feeds, while origin/main added BinanceWebSocketClient and technical indicator functions (calculate_rsi, calculate_macd, get_order_book_imbalance, get_market_data, get_fallback_btc_price). Both implementations are complementary - BinanceWebSocket provides structured BTCPriceData output while BinanceWebSocketClient supports backward compatibility and technical indicators. Merged module docstrings to reflect all capabilities. Updated README to include test_binance_websocket.py test file.
